definitions.definition: The process of extracting useful or valuable materials from used nuclear fuel , mainly focusing on the recovery of fissile and fertile material for use in fresh nuclear reactor fuel , or, in some cases, the manufacture of nuclear weapons .

secondary_definitions: ( engineering , nuclear physics , uncountable ) The process of extracting useful or valuable materials from used nuclear fuel , mainly focusing on the recovery of fissile and fertile material for use in fresh nuclear reactor fuel , or, in some cases, the manufacture of nuclear weapons .
